title: More than 140 injured in clashes between Eritrean asylum seekers and Israeli police
description: More than 140 people have been wounded in clashes between Eritrean asylum seekers and Israeli police in Tel Aviv.

title: Nobel foundation withdraws Russia, Belarus and Iran invitations after 'strong reactions'
description: The Nobel Foundation has withdrawn its invitation to representatives from Russia, Belarus, and Iran to attend this year's Nobel Prize award ceremonies after the controversial decision "provoked strong reactions".

title: Icebreaker sent to Antarctic station to rescue expedition member
description: An icebreaker is en route from Australia to an Antarctic research station to rescue an expedition member who is experiencing a medical issue, according to the Australian government.

title: Billie Eilish helped through festival set after plea to fans
description: US superstar Billie Eilish was supported by fans through her Electric Picnic gig after complaining of feeling "really, really sick".

title: Gang-ruled prisons, assassinated politicians and a drug lord's killing in Ecuador
description: A mass hostage taking in Ecuador's gang-ruled prisons and the assassination of a politician are the latest bloody episodes in a country gripped by the cocaine trade.

title: Sir Elton John leads tributes after singer-songwriter and billionaire businessman Jimmy Buffett dies
description: Sir Elton John has led tributes to the US singer-songwriter Jimmy Buffett, who died at the age of 76 on Friday.

title: Prison inmates release guards and police after 57 taken hostage in Ecuador
description: Dozens of guards and police have been released after a series of hostage situations in Ecuador's prisons.

title: India launches first mission to the sun
description: Ten days after India's success in landing the first ever spacecraft on the southern side of the moon, the country has launched 'Aditya L1', its first mission to study the sun.

title: Is Saudi Arabia's growing football empire really a threat to the Premier League?
description: In Monte Carlo - where wealth is flaunted on Saudi scales - the powerbrokers of European football gathered to party and to plan the season ahead.
